"%1$d. Xiaomi TVs, set-top boxes, projectors: Connect both your mobile device and external monitor to the same WLAN network for best effect. If they are connected to different networks, it might take more time to find the external monitor and connect. Note: Older TV models might not support casting across different networks. %2$d. If you're using TVs, set-top boxes, or projectors of other brands, connect both your mobile device and external monitor to the same WLAN network. If the two devices can't be connected to the same network, turn on Miracast on your external monitor. The naming of Miracast functionality might vary."

"%1$d. Xiaomi-TV-er, set-top-bokser, projektorer: Koble både mobilenheten og den eksterne skjermen til det samme Wi-Fi-nettverket for best resultat. Hvis du bruker TV-er, set-top-bokser eller projektorer av andre merker, kobler du både mobilenheten og den eksterne skjermen til det samme Wi-Fi-nettverket. Hvis de to enhetene ikke kan kobles til det samme nettverket, slår du på Miracast på den eksterne skjermen. Navnet på Miracast-funksjonen kan variere."

If you want to use a Xiaomi device, but can't find it in the list of available devices, try the following: Connect both your mobile device and the external monitor (e.g. your TV) to the same network, or connect the external monitor to your mobile device's hotspot. If there aren't any networks available or you can't connect both devices to the same network, check whether the casting features on your external monitor are up to date, turn on Bluetooth both on your mobile device and the external monitor, and turn on Miracast on your TV. %2$d.
